          <text>
                    <body>
                              <pb n="1"/>
                              <p rend="align(right)">
                                        <placeName>San Francisco</placeName>
                                        <date>Dec. 31. 1853</date>
                              </p>
                              <p>
                                        <addressee>Mr Isaac Leeser</addressee>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(2)">Dear Friend</p>
                              <p rend="indent(4)">I send you again a few<lb/> subscribers to the
                                        “Occident,” which I have procured<lb/> since my last, of the
                                                  <date>15<hi rend="sup">th</hi></date> Inst.</p>
                              <p>I also send you 8 copies of the “Alta California”, and the
                                        “Whey”<lb/> which contains several items of Discussion upon
                                        the Ob-<lb/>-servance of the <date>Sabbath</date> &amp;c, by
                                        the perusal of which, you<lb/> will notice, that we do not
                                        allow our Religion to be<lb/> slandered even out here on
                                        these <placeName>western Shores</placeName>, &amp; are<lb/>
                                        always ready to defend our proud and sacred Faith.<lb/>
                                        You'll read those Articles (I marked them with a black<lb/>
                                        rounding) &amp; form then your own Idea about them<lb/>
                                        There was nothing else, concerning Jewish Affairs,
                                        trans-<lb/>-pired to my knowledge; I shall always
                                        endeavor<lb/> to keep you posted up <del>whenever</del> on
                                        any thing of any<lb/> Importance to you, what may occur
                                        here, &amp; which may serve<lb/> as Interesting News in your
                                        Occident.</p>
                              <p>The Rainy Season is very severe this year, beyond all<lb/>
                                        Expectations, &amp; it is for that Reason, that
                                        Merchants<lb/> did fail in laying in sufficient supplies for
                                        the<lb/> winter, and the consequence is in some mines,
                                        that<lb/> miners have to suffer very much for want of
                                        provisions.<lb/> For all other local affairs I refer you to
                                        the Papers.</p>
                              <pb n="2"/>
                              <p>I enjoy, thank God, good Health, hope you may enjoy<lb/> the same
                                        Blessing; but Business has moderated greatly, yet<lb/> we
                                        console ourselves with bright prospects.</p>
                              <p>Let me soon hear from you again.</p>
                              <p>Accept the best wishes for your Health &amp; Happiness</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">from</p>
                              <p rend="indent(2)">Yours Truly</p>
                              <p rend="indent(4)">
                                        <persName role="author">C H Meyers</persName>
                              </p>
                              <p>N. B. <persName>Mr. Roggenburger</persName> &amp; Family<lb/>
                                        desire their kind Regards to you</p>
                    </body>
